#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn4.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. Life Span "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn4.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Subhasutta "
msgstr "3. Beautiful "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts2ed1.234, sc1
msgctxt "sn4.3:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn4.3:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā uruvelāyaṃ viharati najjā nerañjarāya tīre ajapālanigrodhamūle paṭhamābhisambuddho. "
msgstr "At one time, when he was first awakened, the Buddha was staying near Uruvelā at the root of the goatherd’s banyan tree on the bank of the Nerañjarā River. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.3:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā rattandhakāratimisāyaṃ abbhokāse nisinno hoti, devo ca ekamekaṃ phusāyati. "
msgstr "Now at that time the Buddha was meditating in the open during the dark of night, while a gentle rain drizzled down. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: The phrase is identical with SN 2.29, and i don’t see why we should follow BB in using “color” there and “shape” here for vanna.
msgctxt "sn4.3:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā, bhagavato bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃsaṃ uppādetukāmo, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato avidūre uccāvacā vaṇṇanibhā upadaṃseti, subhā ceva asubhā ca. "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked, wanting to make the Buddha feel fear, terror, and goosebumps, approached him, and while not far away generated a rainbow of bright colors, both beautiful and ugly. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.3:1.5"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, replied to him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn4.3:2.1"
msgid "“Saṃsaraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ, "
msgstr "“Transmigrating for such a long time, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.3:2.2"
msgid "vaṇṇaṃ katvā subhāsubhaṃ; "
msgstr "you’ve made forms beautiful and ugly. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.3:2.3"
msgid "Alaṃ te tena pāpima, "
msgstr "Enough of this, Wicked One! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.3:2.4"
msgid "nihato tvamasi antaka. "
msgstr "You’re beaten, terminator. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn4.3:3.1"
msgid "Ye ca kāyena vācāya, "
msgstr "Those who are well restrained "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.3:3.2"
msgid "manasā ca susaṃvutā; "
msgstr "in body, speech, and mind "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.3:3.3"
msgid "Na te māravasānugā, "
msgstr "don’t fall under Māra’s sway, "

# NOTE: See BB for reading.
#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: baddhagū → paccagū (si, s1-3, km, pts1) | paddhagūti (pts2) | baddhabhū (mr)
msgctxt "sn4.3:3.4"
msgid "na te mārassa baddhagū”ti. "
msgstr "they don’t become your footmen.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn4.3:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro … pe … tatthevantaradhāyīti. "
msgstr "Then Māra … vanished right there."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
